<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-09-08T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-09-08T18:00:00-05:00" n="1158" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1158">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.113/930.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul at
                                    Nogales</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Douglas Ariz.</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-09-08T16:00:00-07:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 8, 1912—4 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>I have just forwarded to Naco the arms and ammunition for consular agent
                            Cananea by the same train it arrived on; it can not be forwarded
                            immediately to Cananea from Naco because about 200 rebels have taken
                            possession of railroad. There are now 500 Federals at Cananea, with 400
                            more en route to Cananea from Nogales; apparently there is no danger of
                            Cananea being captured, and arms and ammunition can remain in the
                            possession of United States troops Naco for the present.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Dye.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>